Run Server:

python group_chat.py


Enter server when prompted.

Server starts and waits for clients.

Run Clients:

Open new terminals for each client.

Run:

python group_chat.py


Enter client and provide a username.

Chat:

Type messages and press Enter.

Messages are broadcast to all connected clients.

Exit:

Closing a client notifies others: username left the chat.

Notes: Use 127.0.0.1 for local testing or LAN IP for multiple devices. Default port is 5000.
